I don't think anyone knows to that level.
Only genetic component we've seen is twins
Both sets of twins we've seen where one had the spark, both had the spark.
Who are the other twins?
Ugin/Bolas
Sparks can be given up, transferred, extracted, etc. About the only thing we haven't seen is copying a spark.
Ah, didn't think of that
Good point
Or artificial sparks, I don't think.
The twins share a spark, and aren’t Planeswalkers yet, as of the set.
They spark at the end of the story

In this case they somehow 'share' the spark. I don't know how that works, unless there's some kind of 'quantum entanglement' involved.
Without spoiling anything, the twins are different than Bolas/Ugin because they latter have two separate sparks where as the Twins have to planeswalk together. That is explained though.

text: and that requires a tap

Right - that's what makes this so interesting to me.
It's a relevant mana sink on a common.
and 2R isn't overcosted.
Is it an awesome card? No, of course not; but it is a cheap and interesting option for the right deck.
It's one of those cards that makes me realize how amazing the game is since here we are 25+ years later and they're still doing new things.
It's going in my Squee deck, I know, but I'm not sure that it will be useful in a lot of other places.
It's fairly niche, but I could see decks that care about rummage/discard or creatures to jump on it.
Anything with a repeatable activated ability that says 'draw a card' will be relevant in certain decks for sure.
I could see this in some [[marisil the pretender]] decks.
